    "faq": {
      "type": "lsc-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "what is laser hair removal?",
            "answer": "<p>Laser hair removal is a medical-grade treatment that uses targeted light energy to reduce unwanted hair growth at the root. The laser safely heats the hair follicle, disrupting future growth while protecting the surrounding skin.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does laser hair removal work?",
            "answer": "<p>The laser emits controlled pulses of light that are absorbed by pigment in the hair. This energy travels down to the follicle and reduces its ability to produce new hair.</p><p>Because hair grows in cycles, only active follicles can be treated at each session which is why a structured course is required.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients require a course of 6–8 sessions spaced 4–6 weeks apart, depending on:</p><p>• Area treated</p><p>• Hair thickness</p><p>• Hair growth cycle</p><p>• Hormonal influences</p><p>Your personalised treatment plan is discussed at consultation so you know exactly what to expect.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why are multiple sessions required?",
            "answer": "<p>Hair grows in different phases. The laser is most effective during the active growth phase.</p><p>Each session targets a new group of follicles entering that phase, which is why treatments are spaced out in a structured course.</p><p>This approach delivers safe, long-term reduction rather than short-term results.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is laser hair removal permanent?",
            "answer": "<p>Laser hair removal provides long-term hair reduction.</p><p>Most clients experience significant, lasting reduction in treated areas. Some may require occasional maintenance sessions depending on hormonal factors or hair type.</p><p>We focus on realistic, transparent expectations from the start.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "does the treatment hurt?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients describe the sensation as a quick, warm snap against the skin.</p><p>Modern medical lasers include built-in cooling systems to improve comfort. Treatment settings are adjusted to your tolerance while maintaining effectiveness.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is it safe for my skin tone?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We use advanced medical-grade laser systems suitable for a wide range of skin tones.</p><p>Your consultation includes a skin assessment and patch test to ensure safe, appropriate settings before full treatment begins.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_8": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can hormonal hair growth affect results?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Conditions such as PCOS or hormonal fluctuations can influence hair growth patterns.</p><p>Laser can still be highly effective, but some clients may require maintenance sessions. This is discussed clearly during consultation so you have realistic expectations.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_9": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What areas can be treated?",
            "answer": "<p>Common areas include:</p><p>• Underarms</p><p>• Bikini & Hollywood</p><p>• Legs</p><p>• Face (upper lip, chin, jawline)</p><p>• Back & chest</p><p>We tailor settings depending on the area and hair type.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_10": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What happens at my consultation?",
            "answer": "<p>Your consultation includes:</p><p>• Skin and hair assessment</p><p>• Medical history review</p><p>• Patch test</p><p>• Discussion of expected sessions</p><p>• Clear pricing overview</p><p>You’ll leave knowing exactly how the process works and whether laser is right for you.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_11": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I shave between sessions?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes shaving is recommended between treatments.</p><p>Avoid waxing, plucking, or threading during your course, as these remove the follicle needed for the laser to work effectively.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_12": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will I need maintenance sessions?",
            "answer": "<p>Some clients choose occasional maintenance treatments once or twice per year, especially in hormonally sensitive areas.</p><p>Your long-term plan is discussed openly so there are no surprises.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_13": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What payment options do you offer?",
            "answer": "<p>We offer flexible payment options to make your treatment as convenient as possible. You can choose to pay per single session or pay in full for a course of treatments for better overall value. We accept card, cash, and bank transfer in clinic.</p><p>For added flexibility, we also offer 0% finance through Klarna, allowing you to spread the cost into manageable instalments with a range of payment options available, subject to eligibility.</p><p>If you’re unsure which option is best for you, our team will be happy to guide you.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_14": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I already had a patch test elsewhere do I need another one?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes we must conduct our own patch test before treatment can start.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_15": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I would like to speak to someone before I book my treatment, how is best to do this?",
            "answer": "<p>If you would like to speak to someone please do one of the below.<br/><br/>- Use the enquiry button.<br/><br/>- Contact us via email at info@laserskinclinics.co.uk<br/><br/>- Call us during opening hours on 01902 256667<br/><br/>- Send us a WhatsApp by clicking the WhatsApp button on the website.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_16": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is your cancellation policy?",
            "answer": "<p>Cancellations up to 24 hours before your appointment can be rescheduled.<br/><br/>Any cancellations on the day will lose that session out of the course booking No shows will be treated the same.<br/><br/>Please note that we offer email and text appointment reminders right up until 24 hours before your appointment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_17": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there any downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>No downtime is required. You might experience mild redness or sensitivity for a few hours after treatment, but this quickly subsides, allowing you to resume your normal routine straight away.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_18": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What should I do before my treatment?",
            "answer": "<p>We recommend shaving the treatment area 24 hours before your session and avoiding sun exposure or fake tan for at least two weeks prior.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_19": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results last?",
            "answer": "<p>Results are long-lasting, once a follicle is disabled, it will not regrow. Some clients may need occasional maintenance sessions to treat any fine or regrown hairs over time</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_20": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is the treatment painful?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients describe the feeling as a quick, warm flick against the skin, much more comfortable than waxing. Our advanced laser systems include cooling technology to minimise any discomfort during treatment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_21": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>For best results, most clients require between 6 and 8 sessions. Hair grows in cycles, so multiple treatments ensure we target every follicle at the right stage of growth.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_22": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can all skin types be treated?",
            "answer": "<p>Absolutely. Our advanced laser systems are suitable for a wide range of skin tones and hair types. During your consultation, we’ll assess your skin and create a personalised treatment plan.</p>"
          }
        }
